                        <r3d:remarks>RADAR4Chem is based on the well-established data repository RADAR run by FIZ Karlsruhe - Leibniz Institute for Information Infrastructure (https://www.re3data.org/repository/r3d100012330). It was developed within the framework of FIZ Karlsruhe´s participation in the chemistry consortium NFDI4Chem (funded by German Research Foundation (DFG) - 441958208) within the german Nationale Forschungsdateninfrastruktur (NFDI). RADAR4Chem serves as a catch-all repository, which complements the already existing portfolio of subject specific repositories for chemistry research data and is e.g. ideally suited for cross-disciplinary data or datasets with a multitude of different data formats.</r3d:remarks>
